3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the use of Software Defined Radios to carry out road traffic poisoning attacks, which involves manipulating network traffic. 
4. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems): The paper discusses different adversary models and tools used in road traffic poisoning attacks, which can be seen as a form of multiagent systems. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes novel countermeasures to mitigate the threats posed by road traffic poisoning, which involves the use of AI techniques such as machine learning.
